"{\"uid\": \"newsaf.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-11-China-retain-women-s-table-tennis-team-gold-at-Paris-Olympics-1vXH70dpuYU-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  China's women's table tennis team defended their title at Paris Olympics after crushing Japan 3-0 on Saturday.  With the trio of Chen Meng, Sun Yingsha and Wang Manyu, China triumphed after a sequence of one doubles and two singles matches against Japan's Hina Hayata, Miwa Harimoto and Miu Hirano.  The victory marked China's fifth consecutive women's team title since the event was introduced at the 2008 Beijing Olympics.  After winning the women's team gold, China completed a clean sweep of the Olympic gold medals in table tennis in Paris.  This gold medal also marked China's 300th gold medal in summer Olympic Games.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"